// Create SparkSession
Logger.getLogger("org").setLevel(Level.ERROR)
val spark = SparkSession.builder()
.master("local[*]")
.appName("Uber clustering")
.getOrCreate()
import spark.implicits._

//Create the schema
val schema = StructType(Array(
                 StructField("Date/Time",StringType,true),
                 StructField("Lat", DoubleType,true),
                 StructField("Lon", DoubleType,true),
                 StructField("Base", StringType, true)
                 ))

//Load csv data for every month from April to September
val df_apr = spark.read.option("header", true).schema(schema)
  .csv("file:///usr/zeppelin/uber-raw-data-apr14.csv")
val df_may = spark.read.option("header", true).schema(schema)
.csv("file:///usr/zeppelin/uber-raw-data-may14.csv")
  
val df_jun = spark.read.option("header", true).schema(schema)
.csv("file:///usr/zeppelin/uber-raw-data-jun14.csv")

val df_jul = spark.read.option("header", true).schema(schema)
.csv("file:///usr/zeppelin/uber-raw-data-jul14.csv")

val df_aug = spark.read.option("header", true).schema(schema)
.csv("file:///usr/zeppelin/uber-raw-data-aug14.csv")

val df_sep = spark.read.option("header", true).schema(schema)
.csv("file:///usr/zeppelin/uber-raw-data-sep14.csv")

%sql
select Lat, Lon FROM df_uber

// This view does not really help us to set a good number of clusters. So we will set a relatively high number of clusters to retrieve the maximum information
// Let's say K = 10

import org.apache.spark.ml.feature.VectorAssembler
import org.apache.spark.ml.clustering.KMeans

// K-means clustering
val featureCols = Array("Lat", "Lon")
val assembler = new VectorAssembler().setInputCols(featureCols).setOutputCol("features")
val df_uber2 = assembler.transform(df_uber)
val kmeans = new KMeans().setK(10).setFeaturesCol("features").setPredictionCol("cluster")

val model = kmeans.fit(df_uber2)
println("Final clusters centers:")
model.clusterCenters.foreach(println)
